fields.data: black
I can't let it rot any longer...
It's so been long since...

Got my hot cocoa and comfy slippers.
My fleece cover. Full laptop battery.
And proper couch sitting position.

IT WILL HAPPEN TODAY
~~ manifesting ~~
That's an admin folder.
Hhmmmm... I should get back to writing...

let netflix = FIELD_OR_LIBRARY("pic");
await SHOW_IMAGE("background", netflix, 2, 0,0);
HIDE_IMAGE("background");

let netflix = FIELD_OR_LIBRARY("pic2");

I should clean this folder one of these days...
One of the many backups. Not losing another game again...

What's in there?
...
Yeah... Let's not touch that.
I think I cleaned that not that long ago?
That's... a really old version. I should probably trash it at some point...
Don't need to open that. The decompiled files are in that folder.
Some test code for future interactivity. Not relevant to this chapter.

That's the map of the house. I spent so long working on it...
I should have made it smaller...

The writing file. With all the writing. The file with the writing.
I should open the program first, or it will crash again.

The map of the city. So many neighbourhoods, so many ideas...
So little time.

The amazing portrait of Prince V, what I won a while back. I still can't believe I lucky I got.
One day I'll be able to commission the rest of the cast.

The notes for the next chapter. It all clear, all the beats are there.
I can even imagine the scenes so clearly!

Humph... what's this doing here...
Wrong project.

The copy of the previous chapters, just the writing.
I'm afraid of opening it and seeing embarrassing typos again...

All the code is in there. All the bugs too...
But I should open VSCode first, otherwise it will load weird...

My notes for the game. A general outline for the story. It's 5 Acts, with more branches than I care to admit.
Will it ever get done? Am I lying to myself?

Notes on the different characters. Their backstories, their goals, their quests, their wants, and some random stuff...
I hope I do them justice.
Some inspirational(-ish) moodboards. Not very... inspirational right now.
The list of variables, choices and variation. And the ones to come.
What's that word for...

Well, this is embarrassing.
Can't remember the word for "accueil" in English...

What would I *even* do without a translator...
Nothing, that's why!
Still, won't be able to fix my typos... :/

Oooh... A bazillion notifications! 
...
Ah, well. Just jam notifications then.
One little game wouldn't hurt... You learn so much from playing games.

Mmmh...
I really thought people would like that game.

Let's maybe put on some music to get into the ~~mood~~...
Or maybe I can just quickly check...

Ok, last time I spent an hour scrolling through the Shorts. This time I won't...
Even if that video essay about some obscure thing...

It's another hour later.
I swear I'm not procrastinating!

Spam, AI spam, spam...
Notifications from the Forum...

People joining the jams...
More spam...
Some weirdo talking about a new sys- oh no, that's some crypto bs.

Reminder of a deadline...
Friend dropped a game! (shouldn't forget to play)
Spam...

Got new Tumblr mes--
mmh... Another one for the block list, I guess...

I spend way too much time looking up old games and reviews. There's so much it's a bit overwhelming.
I'll still try to play as many as I can... It's cause I want to!

Oh! A new review! A treat!!
Aaawww... they liked my game!
Yes... thank you, VSCode... I know I have 9+ errors on this page. And actually, I have more. A whole spreadsheet.
Nightmare. An absolute nightmare.
Where did this even come from?!?
I just want to throw this whole thing away...
Why did I think this would be a good idea?!!?
That is so wrong... WHY DID I DOD THIS?!?!
How was this reported as a bug?

I don't get it... It should work-
Oh... OH... Oh, no...
I swear I fixed this before!

How is this still a bug?!
I know I fixed... 
WHAT
absolute hell... i am in coding hell...
Oh... well, I guess this one was easy.
the previous chapter. it's already online.
Mmmh... That... wasn't too bad. I should have maybe edited it a bit more.
oh, how I missed you, count!
maybe i should have written from your perspective...
cringe. absolute cringe. how did I think it would not just work but...
honestly, it's just shameful. pure and simple.

reading is fundamental...
and i obviously... can't even read my own work!
urhg... it's so bad.
will this need a re-write?
it will, won't it...

:/
i don't like this anymore...
the next chapter of the story. still just a draft...
Let's get writing! It's just words... one after the other...
Come oooonnn, words... let's get on the page!
It doesn't have to be good. Or bad. Just one word.

Please... It's not supposed to be that hard. I've done it before.
I want to do it again...
Well... I did my best... I think...
